  <preparation>Heat half &amp; half in double boiler until hot but not boiling.  Beat egg yolks, sugar and salt and gradually add hotg half &amp; half.  Put mixture into baking dish and put into preheated oven at 350F and bake until set.  Test like custard.  Put in refrigerator until cool.  Sprinkle a thin layer of brown sugar on top and put under the broiler  Let brown sugar melt.  Watch closely or it will burn.

Take 2 boxes of fresh strawberries. Mix 1 tablespoon of honey, and 2 Tablespoons of Kirsh and serve with creme Broulet, or can be served with canned green gage plums.</preparation>
